        <p id="JRPG">JRPG</p>

        <h2><b>Final Fantasy VII :</b></h2>
        <p>Now I have to say, this is my favorite game. I have played it more time than I could ever keep track. I
            highly recommend this game. Not only was it iconic for the time it came out (1997) but it still stands
            strong to this day.</p>
        <img src="https://i.redd.it/9branstdv5p21.jpg" alt="ff7" />
        <br />


        <h2><b>Final Fantasy XII The Zodiac Age :</b></h2>
        <p>This just might be my second favorite Final Fantasy game. I have played the origional back in the day and the
            remastered Zodiac Age edition. I also highly recommend this game, in my opinion it is very underated. The
            gambit system is a lot like if, else statements, so code monkeys should be able to grasp the concept pretty
            quickly.</p>
        <div id="img-div">
            <img id="image"
                src="https://th.bing.com/th/id/R.85d167e6b77145bdd68a8c99dec51117?rik=2D8vRMNtVDVyZg&riu=http%3a%2f%2fayay.co.uk%2fbackgrounds%2frpg_games%2ffinal_fantasy_12%2fcast-of-ff-XII-sitting-around-a-tree.jpg&ehk=kkYcU%2bXoJuAZCHec56yGPL8o9zyWS5csrR9yIMZQ33A%3d&risl=&pid=ImgRaw&r=0"
                alt="ff12" />
            <div id="img-caption">ff12 cast</div>
        </div>



        <h2><b>Final Fantasy XV :</b></h2>
        <p>I am not going to lie, it took me a while for this game to grow on me. Now I cannot get enough of it. You
            definitely need to buy and play the DLC to get the full experience (which I am not a fan of) but I place it
            on my must play list reguardless.</p>
        <img src="https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/5/5a/FF_XV_cover_art.jpg" alt="ff15" />
        <br />



        <h2><b>Gravity Rush :</b></h2>
        <p>I platniumed this game it was that good. The game mechanics are so origional. The world and characters are
            fresh and not over used concepts. Plus it has a classic quirky anime humor I really love. A JRPG you cannot
            miss!</p>
        <img src="https://external-preview.redd.it/dc7lIlyOXlv70Z0xSTn0zm0FJS02PgKi6W7ND9Q2ai4.jpg?auto=webp&s=451cf9979ef3ba9776ccfd524a2d15cbcd89ccae"
            alt="gravityRush" />

        <br />


        <p id="FPS">FPS</p>
        <br />



        <h2><b>Borderlands 1, 2, 3 & Presequel</b></h2>
        <br />
        <p>Yea that is right, I listed all of them, they are all worth playing for their own reason. BL2 is my personal
            favorite but I recommend you play them all with all the DLC</p>
        <img src="https://i.redd.it/d0xyfucxxkl31.jpg" alt="BL2" />
        <br />


        <h2><b>Halo</b></h2>
        <p>Again, the whole series, you have to experience all of it. This is a legendary FPS that really put XBOX on
            the map. I personally only bought a XBOX console to play Halo alone. Just play it.
        </p>
        <img src="https://i.redd.it/3uamclzcrcn11.jpg" alt="halo" />

        <p id="RPG">RPG</p>
        <br />
        <h2><b>Skyrim</b></h2>
        <p>This game has stolen so much of my life and I do not mind one bit. This highly addictive game will overwhelm
            you with a dense map and tons of character development. You will want to keep coming back to slay or ride a
            dragon.</p>
